3
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:45,490
Jang Ho Woo, the question you asked me earlier...

4
00:00:45,490 --> 00:00:48,253
I'll answer you right now.

5
00:00:48,253 --> 00:00:50,223
What do I gain?

6
00:00:51,763 --> 00:00:53,873
It's a wild card.

7
00:00:53,873 --> 00:00:56,953
a card that isn't anything, but can also become anything,

8
00:00:56,953 --> 00:01:00,823
an unpredictable card that can overturn a game

9
00:01:00,823 --> 00:01:03,333
with a clear winner.

10
00:01:03,333 --> 00:01:06,143
You mean like a Joker in a trump card game?

11
00:01:06,143 --> 00:01:10,683
I guess you are a Joker since I can't tell what you're thinking, from your appearance.

12
00:01:10,683 --> 00:01:15,643
Then again, I suppose a trump card game has two Jokers.

13
00:01:15,643 --> 00:01:20,353
So with that said, Jang Ho Woo, you should join my team.

14
00:01:26,713 --> 00:01:28,773
I don't want to.

15
00:01:44,583 --> 00:01:47,253
The coffee from the company café tastes really good.

16
00:01:47,253 --> 00:01:49,343
The employee reviews are good, as well.

17
00:01:49,343 --> 00:01:52,793
Even the people who initially opposed you in

18
00:01:52,793 --> 00:01:55,423
 hiring a barista with hearing loss now favor it. 

19
00:01:55,423 --> 00:02:00,743
I was happy that I'd be working in the president's secretary's office when Vice President An Seung Yeon became President.

20
00:02:00,743 --> 00:02:02,063
But what's this?

21
00:02:02,063 --> 00:02:04,133
You know, she has cardiovascular disease.

22
00:02:04,133 --> 00:02:07,763
It's her health, nothing else; not much can be done.

23
00:02:10,993 --> 00:02:12,633
She can't hear us.

24
00:02:12,633 --> 00:02:14,643
Oh, that's right.

25
00:02:14,643 --> 00:02:18,063
Well, it's because they can talk freely

26
00:02:18,063 --> 00:02:22,250
without anyone listening to their conversations.

27
00:02:22,953 --> 00:02:26,973
Looks like People's Entertainment's audit is almost completed as well.

28
00:02:26,973 --> 00:02:30,693
I believe it will wrap up as soon as the financial institutions' confirmation letters are collected.

29
00:02:30,693 --> 00:02:34,183
Well, from the banks' perspectives,

30
00:02:34,183 --> 00:02:38,043
it could seem a hassle to provide confirmation letters.

31
00:02:38,043 --> 00:02:41,553
Since this has nothing to do with them, even if they provide one,

32
00:02:41,553 --> 00:02:43,813
there's not much to gain from this.

33
00:02:43,813 --> 00:02:46,793
I will do my best to keep track of the situation.

34
00:02:48,903 --> 00:02:53,113
As you run for president, the person to watch for is 
    

35
00:02:53,113 --> 00:02:55,893
Vice President An Seung Yeon of the Audit Department.

36
00:02:55,893 --> 00:02:59,893
- If you look at this— 
 - No need to be concerned about Vice President An.

37
00:02:59,893 --> 00:03:06,433
It seems she will have a more urgent matter than becoming President of Taeil Accounting.

38
00:03:06,433 --> 00:03:08,843
Instead of that,

39
00:03:08,843 --> 00:03:13,973
let's plant someone as a spy inside People's Entertainment's audit team.

40
00:03:13,973 --> 00:03:16,043
You never know with these things.

41
00:03:16,043 --> 00:03:20,433
Think of it as installing a CCTV.

42
00:03:22,453 --> 00:03:24,943
Yes, I understand.

43
00:03:26,033 --> 00:03:29,063
Why don't you want to?

44
00:03:29,063 --> 00:03:31,613
Do you think you'll just be making photocopies or something?

45
00:03:31,613 --> 00:03:33,803
I won't make you do things like that. Don't worry.

46
00:03:33,803 --> 00:03:37,403
It's not that I'm worried; I just refuse.

47
00:03:39,833 --> 00:03:44,053
Any new employee at Taeil Accounting Firm will want to work on my team.

48
00:03:44,053 --> 00:03:45,133
What's wrong with you?

49
00:03:45,133 --> 00:03:47,853
My risk if I am under your erratic personality,

50
00:03:47,853 --> 00:03:51,313
your unknown competency even with your reputation as V.P. Han Je Gyun's son,

51
00:03:51,313 --> 00:03:53,783
your team's culture I have seen though not experienced it,

52
00:03:53,783 --> 00:03:57,113
and natural dread of uncertainty...

53
00:03:57,113 --> 00:04:01,463
You must know these things very well as an experienced accountant.

54
00:04:02,283 --> 00:04:05,953
If you're done talking, I'll get going now.

55
00:04:21,393 --> 00:04:25,393
   

56
00:04:26,313 --> 00:04:27,973
 But what's this? 

57
00:04:27,973 --> 00:04:30,983
 You know, she has cardiovascular disease. 

58
00:04:30,983 --> 00:04:34,703
 It's her health, nothing else; not much can be done. 

59
00:04:36,183 --> 00:04:40,783
 If Vice President An Seung Yeon resigns soon, then what happens to us? 

60
00:04:40,783 --> 00:04:46,383
   

61
00:04:53,093 --> 00:04:54,263
 Thank you. 

62
00:04:54,263 --> 00:04:56,183
   

63
00:05:03,063 --> 00:05:07,443
What do you mean the financial institutions' confirmation letters haven't arrived yet?

64
00:05:07,443 --> 00:05:14,633
We need them to verify whether People's Entertainment's liability amount is accurate.

65
00:05:14,633 --> 00:05:18,073
 Without the confirmation letters, the audit and reports are completely useless! 

66
00:05:18,073 --> 00:05:21,453
 How many times have I told you to pay attention to this? 

67
00:05:21,453 --> 00:05:23,730
Everything else is ready,

68
00:05:23,730 --> 00:05:27,630
but we're only missing one from Geumyang Joongang Town Fund...

69
00:05:28,433 --> 00:05:32,943
Don't you know that missing one letter is the same as missing them all?

70
00:05:32,943 --> 00:05:34,893
Yes, that's true.

71
00:05:36,013 --> 00:05:38,863
Just how careless were you with this task?

72
00:05:38,863 --> 00:05:41,963
What could we do if they wouldn't give it to us when we went all the way there?

73
00:05:41,963 --> 00:05:44,253
They said the manager wasn't there or they weren't ready yet.

74
00:05:44,253 --> 00:05:47,243
It drives me crazy, too, that they treat me as a fool!

75
00:05:47,243 --> 00:05:49,333
But you still should have gotten it somehow!

76
00:05:49,333 --> 00:05:52,403
Should I have kissed their butts while they purposely delayed?

77
00:05:52,403 --> 00:05:53,923
Yes, if necessary!

78
00:05:53,923 --> 00:05:55,653
Don't you think you're out of line?

79
00:05:55,653 --> 00:05:57,033
Come on, Mr. Choi.

80
00:05:57,033 --> 00:06:00,633
I'm just saying that's not why I became an accountant.

81
00:06:00,633 --> 00:06:01,963
I got it. I got it.

82
00:06:01,963 --> 00:06:04,243
I'll do it.

83
00:06:11,053 --> 00:06:13,263
I'm Jang Ho Woo, the new recruit.

84
00:06:13,263 --> 00:06:16,223
With your permission, I'll go down to Geumyang now

85
00:06:16,223 --> 00:06:20,283
and be sure to bring back the financial institution's confirmation letter.

86
00:06:31,123 --> 00:06:34,013
- Welcome. 
 - Hello.

87
00:06:35,760 --> 00:06:37,373
   

88
00:06:37,373 --> 00:06:39,673
One cray double sandwich, please—

89
00:06:39,673 --> 00:06:43,083
I'm telling you. Don't order a cray double sandwich.

90
00:06:43,083 --> 00:06:44,963
It's not good.

91
00:06:44,963 --> 00:06:48,863
What are you doing, ordering that at a roast beef sandwich shop?

92
00:06:48,863 --> 00:06:51,733
Please give me two roast beef sandwiches.

93
00:07:00,413 --> 00:07:02,473
I'm wearing sneakers to conduct due diligence.

94
00:07:02,473 --> 00:07:05,170
You do know what due diligence is, right?

95
00:07:05,833 --> 00:07:09,753
The process of verifying the actuality of the—

96
00:07:09,753 --> 00:07:11,553
What are those documents?

97
00:07:11,553 --> 00:07:13,433
It's my first duty as a new recruit.

98
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:16,433
I have to go to another city in a hurry.

99
00:07:23,903 --> 00:07:26,653
I'll give you a ride; you can eat on the way.

100
00:07:26,653 --> 00:07:30,133
If you eat like that, you'll be in trouble even before you get there.

101
00:07:30,133 --> 00:07:32,623
- Do you even know where I'm going now? 
 - It's written there: Geumyang.

102
00:07:32,623 --> 00:07:34,843
I'm going in the same direction.

103
00:07:44,633 --> 00:07:46,683
   

104
00:07:49,313 --> 00:07:52,143
   

105
00:08:00,923 --> 00:08:03,693
   

106
00:08:10,933 --> 00:08:14,013
   

107
00:08:15,453 --> 00:08:17,443
Thank you.

108
00:08:21,393 --> 00:08:23,223
Thanks to you—

109
00:08:30,813 --> 00:08:34,673
I'm from Taeil Accounting in Seoul. I'm here to get a confirmation letter.

110
00:08:34,673 --> 00:08:36,243
Take a number, please.

111
00:08:36,243 --> 00:08:39,353
You just need to check People's Entertainment's balance and loan amount for me.

112
00:08:39,353 --> 00:08:41,953
Didn't you hear me say, "Take a number and wait"?

113
00:08:41,953 --> 00:08:43,903
Are we your minions or something?

114
00:08:43,903 --> 00:08:46,163
I have to work late even after we close for the day.

115
00:08:46,163 --> 00:08:49,213
How dare you try to cut in line!

116
00:08:49,993 --> 00:08:53,843
Sir, if you want to withdraw from your savings account, you need to fill this out!

117
00:08:53,843 --> 00:08:56,663
I can't hear you. Speak louder!

118
00:08:56,663 --> 00:08:59,103
What kind of writing is this small?

119
00:08:59,103 --> 00:09:00,803
Ma'am, your I.D., please.

120
00:09:00,803 --> 00:09:04,083
You know who I am! Why do you ask me for that?

121
00:09:04,083 --> 00:09:07,523
We need it to complete the process.

122
00:09:07,523 --> 00:09:10,193
Gosh, come over here!

123
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:17,770
When will it be my turn? I can't wait forever.

124
00:09:17,770 --> 00:09:21,093
- Why is that? 
 - Please take a seat.

125
00:09:24,813 --> 00:09:27,193
He's not sitting still like the other accountants.

126
00:09:27,193 --> 00:09:29,453
Where is he going?

127
00:09:29,453 --> 00:09:34,253
Maybe he gave up already, knowing I won't give him the confirmation letter.

128
00:09:34,253 --> 00:09:36,563
Do you think Jang Ho Woo can get the confirmation letter?

129
00:09:36,563 --> 00:09:39,243
Even a grand master accountant couldn't bring it back.

130
00:09:39,243 --> 00:09:42,343
Do you know how many documents I sent them, including self-addressed envelopes?

131
00:09:42,343 --> 00:09:44,213
One day, I wanted to see who would win.

132
00:09:44,213 --> 00:09:47,863
I sat there all day, but they completely ignored me.

133
00:09:47,863 --> 00:09:49,673
There's no chance.

134
00:09:51,683 --> 00:09:53,783
Here you go.

135
00:09:53,783 --> 00:09:56,953
Is there a place for me to print something in this area?

136
00:09:56,953 --> 00:10:00,153
I'm not sure about that.

137
00:10:02,093 --> 00:10:05,063
There must be a printing service somewhere.

138
00:10:08,643 --> 00:10:10,443
   

139
00:10:12,263 --> 00:10:14,933
- Thank you, Sir. 
 - Sure.

140
00:10:14,933 --> 00:10:17,313
Any news?

141
00:10:17,313 --> 00:10:19,293
No, not yet.

142
00:10:19,293 --> 00:10:22,583
I-I'll try calling him.

143
00:10:28,703 --> 00:10:31,623
   

144
00:10:34,013 --> 00:10:36,133
   

145
00:10:37,983 --> 00:10:39,953
All right, all right!

146
00:10:39,953 --> 00:10:43,973
For those of you who need to withdraw from your account or borrow money,

147
00:10:43,973 --> 00:10:48,873
come to me, and I'll help you fill out the forms and anything else you need!

148
00:10:48,873 --> 00:10:52,783
I'm not someone suspicious. I'm an accountant, an accountant!

149
00:10:52,783 --> 00:10:56,883
The bank teller should be the only one who needs to know our bank account number.

150
00:10:56,883 --> 00:10:58,973
   

151
00:10:58,973 --> 00:11:02,403
As expected, with grandmas and grandpas (older people)...

152
00:11:02,403 --> 00:11:03,693
What did you say?

153
00:11:03,693 --> 00:11:06,883
It seems he turned off his cell phone.

154
00:11:08,193 --> 00:11:11,403
We have only two hours left!

155
00:11:16,273 --> 00:11:18,263
 If you come to me, 

156
00:11:18,263 --> 00:11:22,613
I will pay for all your banking charges that are such a waste of money!

157
00:11:22,613 --> 00:11:24,263
- "Pay the banking charges"? 
 - Why would he do that?

158
00:11:24,263 --> 00:11:26,923
Starting now, I'm paying for ten people only!

159
00:11:26,923 --> 00:11:29,253
Only the first ten people!

160
00:11:29,253 --> 00:11:30,643
M-Me! Me! Me!

161
00:11:30,643 --> 00:11:31,653
Oh, here.

162
00:11:31,653 --> 00:11:33,373
- Here! 
 - Look at this!

163
00:11:33,373 --> 00:11:36,453
All right, please stand in line here!

164
00:11:36,453 --> 00:11:38,453
- Come here! 
 - Slowly, slowly!

165
00:11:38,453 --> 00:11:41,933
- Just a little this way. 
 - Let go.

166
00:11:41,933 --> 00:11:47,103
   

167
00:11:50,623 --> 00:11:54,103
I'll look over it one more time. You brought your I.D.

168
00:11:54,103 --> 00:11:56,843
All right, you can go to the last window.

169
00:11:56,843 --> 00:11:58,883
- You're giving this to me? 
 - Oh, of course.

170
00:11:58,883 --> 00:12:00,573
I'll just check it once for you.

171
00:12:00,573 --> 00:12:02,323
You filled it out well.

172
00:12:02,323 --> 00:12:04,233
You can go to the window right in front.

173
00:12:04,233 --> 00:12:06,643
Hello, Grandma.

174
00:12:09,873 --> 00:12:11,923
There, over there.

175
00:12:11,923 --> 00:12:13,873
You can go where that grandma went earlier.

176
00:12:13,873 --> 00:12:16,573
Hello.

177
00:12:16,573 --> 00:12:19,713
Customer number 462.

178
00:12:19,713 --> 00:12:22,123
It seems the rush is over for you now.

179
00:12:22,123 --> 00:12:25,163
May I please have the institution's confirmation letter?

180
00:12:35,633 --> 00:12:38,533
As you can see, we close in one minute.

181
00:12:38,533 --> 00:12:40,803
If you come back tomorrow, I'll give it to you then.

182
00:12:40,803 --> 00:12:43,463
It takes some time to complete the financial institution's confirmation letter.

183
00:12:43,463 --> 00:12:46,410
I knew you'd be busy

184
00:12:46,410 --> 00:12:49,570
so I prepared it in advance for you.

185
00:12:50,463 --> 00:12:52,043
   

186
00:12:57,773 --> 00:12:59,983
   

187
00:13:03,483 --> 00:13:05,603
   

188
00:13:05,603 --> 00:13:08,233
If the information on this confirmation letter is incorrect,

189
00:13:08,233 --> 00:13:11,263
then you can rip up the letter on the spot.

190
00:13:11,263 --> 00:13:15,163
But if you rip it up even though the information

191
00:13:15,163 --> 00:13:18,413
is the same as the one you'll give me tomorrow,

192
00:13:18,413 --> 00:13:20,643
- then that's... 
 - What?

193
00:13:20,643 --> 00:13:23,083
You'd be so embarrassed.

194
00:13:23,083 --> 00:13:25,943
If you don't want to be embarrassed and the letter looks correct,

195
00:13:25,943 --> 00:13:27,913
why don't you simply stamp it?

196
00:13:27,913 --> 00:13:31,153
Let's not trouble each other further.

197
00:13:31,823 --> 00:13:33,973
Let's just end it here.

198
00:13:35,790 --> 00:13:38,880
   

199
00:13:42,333 --> 00:13:43,843
Thank you.

200
00:13:43,843 --> 00:13:46,343
You seem a little different from the other accountants,

201
00:13:46,343 --> 00:13:48,323
seeing how you organized the waiting area.

202
00:13:48,323 --> 00:13:51,123
You're a type of alpha (leader) living as a beta (follower).

203
00:13:51,123 --> 00:13:55,543
I didn't become an accountant so people can treat me with respect.

204
00:13:55,543 --> 00:14:00,603
If the other party takes care of my complaint, I can resolve their problem.

205
00:14:00,603 --> 00:14:03,073
Those are basics of transactions.

206
00:14:04,813 --> 00:14:09,483
Now I'll take this to them and get what I want, too.

207
00:14:16,603 --> 00:14:19,613
Wow, he really got this done.

208
00:14:19,613 --> 00:14:21,023
 Hello. 

209
00:14:21,023 --> 00:14:23,643
Weren't you going to get the confirmation letter this morning?

210
00:14:23,643 --> 00:14:25,673
Well, the thing is...

211
00:14:25,673 --> 00:14:28,593
we don't need to go there anymore.

212
00:14:28,593 --> 00:14:30,683
   

213
00:14:32,483 --> 00:14:36,033
   

214
00:14:39,833 --> 00:14:42,193
- Could you photocopy the first three pages, and... 
 - Yes.

215
00:14:42,193 --> 00:14:44,593
If you look on this side, it says, "Income Statement."

216
00:14:44,593 --> 00:14:46,043
Make seven copies of these too.

217
00:14:46,043 --> 00:14:47,903
Woo Sang Hyun!

218
00:14:48,673 --> 00:14:51,453
- I'll leave this to you. 
 - Yes, I'll take care of it.

219
00:15:06,743 --> 00:15:11,873
Is it true that you brought this financial institution's confirmation letter, Mr. Jang?

220
00:15:13,743 --> 00:15:14,693
Yes.

221
00:15:14,693 --> 00:15:17,763
I-Is there something wrong with it?

222
00:15:17,763 --> 00:15:21,013
If there's a problem, I can go down to Geumyang now—

223
00:15:21,013 --> 00:15:22,833
No.

224
00:15:22,833 --> 00:15:25,783
There's nothing wrong with the document.

225
00:15:25,783 --> 00:15:29,603
I heard they weren't interested in giving it to us when we waited all day in their lounge.

226
00:15:29,603 --> 00:15:32,723
How did you manage to get it from them?

227
00:15:33,653 --> 00:15:35,083
I was lucky.

228
00:15:35,083 --> 00:15:39,783
Then... are you saying we were unlucky all this time?

229
00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:45,293
Anyway, I can breathe easily thanks to you.

230
00:15:45,293 --> 00:15:48,373
Thank you. You worked hard.

231
00:16:02,323 --> 00:16:03,953
Now we have the confirmation letter,

232
00:16:03,953 --> 00:16:07,383
we just have to write up the unqualified opinion, and we'll be done.

233
00:16:07,383 --> 00:16:10,023
Gosh, when are we going to write it up now?

234
00:16:10,023 --> 00:16:13,323
Hey, compared to a disclaimer of opinion, writing an unqualified opinion is easy.

235
00:16:13,323 --> 00:16:15,153
We'll do it in no time!

236
00:16:15,153 --> 00:16:17,133
I'm going to a meeting.

237
00:16:17,133 --> 00:16:20,643
- Yes. 
 - Have a good day.

238
00:16:26,013 --> 00:16:28,353
It seems People's Entertainment's audit must be finishing.

239
00:16:28,353 --> 00:16:32,513
The Deals Department Director seems to take a lot of interest in the Auditing Department.

240
00:16:32,513 --> 00:16:37,203
I just heard that one of my clients bought some of People's Entertainment's stocks; I was curious.

241
00:16:37,203 --> 00:16:42,363
You must know very well that we can't share our client's information with outsiders.

242
00:16:42,363 --> 00:16:45,393
Are you saying that I'm included in those "outsiders"?

243
00:16:46,033 --> 00:16:47,983
You're not on the inside.

244
00:16:47,983 --> 00:16:50,073
And that's a relief.

245
00:16:50,743 --> 00:16:53,713
If this is why you wanted to see me, I'm leaving.

246
00:16:53,713 --> 00:16:56,143
Why don't you add one more person to your team?

247
00:16:57,613 --> 00:17:00,843
There won't be any problem with accepting just one more person.

248
00:17:05,083 --> 00:17:10,063
Isn't it trouble that you want to add another to a team without any problems?

249
00:17:10,063 --> 00:17:14,613
The more accurate description is there was a problem, but it was solved.

250
00:17:14,613 --> 00:17:17,963
I heard you couldn't acquire the financial institution's confirmation letter.

251
00:17:21,083 --> 00:17:25,073
How about Jang Ho Woo? The one who got that confirmation letter?

252
00:17:25,073 --> 00:17:28,183
It seems you already witnessed his skills.

253
00:17:34,803 --> 00:17:37,553
   

254
00:17:44,063 --> 00:17:47,503
There's no way it's always this empty here.

