00:31:50,453 --> 00:31:53,223
Is there a need to distinguish between the two?

423
00:31:54,843 --> 00:31:57,733
I felt someone is a friend or foe

424
00:31:57,733 --> 00:32:00,123
depending on timing, not a person.

425
00:32:00,123 --> 00:32:01,153
What?

426
00:32:01,153 --> 00:32:04,103
If they clash with my timing, they're my foe.

427
00:32:04,103 --> 00:32:07,713
But if they unite with my timing, they're my friend.

428
00:32:07,713 --> 00:32:11,933
So you're saying that based on your timing now, Shim Hyung Woo is your friend,

429
00:32:11,933 --> 00:32:14,023
and I shouldn't get in the way?

430
00:32:16,393 --> 00:32:18,063
Okay.

431
00:32:29,293 --> 00:32:31,763
But you...

432
00:32:31,763 --> 00:32:34,023
Why aren't you hiding things in front of me?

433
00:32:34,023 --> 00:32:36,733
You hide them rather well in front of others.

434
00:32:36,733 --> 00:32:39,993
Why are you so blatantly honest with me?

435
00:32:40,543 --> 00:32:42,623
Do I seem gullible to you?

436
00:32:43,393 --> 00:32:46,933
Or am I trustworthy?

437
00:32:56,683 --> 00:33:01,123
 Mr. Kang, why can't an entertainment company include its movies and goods 

438
00:33:01,123 --> 00:33:04,083
 as part of its inventory of assets? Why do this? 

439
00:33:04,083 --> 00:33:06,193
It's not like we're the only ones who do that!

440
00:33:06,193 --> 00:33:10,023
Then why can't you release those movies?

441
00:33:11,763 --> 00:33:14,823
Because so many competitors are out there. I'll release them soon.

442
00:33:14,823 --> 00:33:16,283
I will sell many of them overseas—

443
00:33:16,283 --> 00:33:21,153
Are you sure you can't release them, or is it that they won't sell?

444
00:33:21,153 --> 00:33:24,573
An entertainment company including its movies and goods in its inventory of assets

445
00:33:24,573 --> 00:33:26,723
isn't a problem under normal circumstances.

446
00:33:26,723 --> 00:33:31,803
However, the movies and goods included as part of People's Entertainment's inventory are...

447
00:33:31,803 --> 00:33:35,853
not real assets, but rather a deception to cover up its losses!

448
00:33:35,853 --> 00:33:38,183
That's the problem!

449
00:33:43,103 --> 00:33:44,933
 Mr. Jang Ho Woo. 

450
00:33:44,933 --> 00:33:49,073
 The news reported that they were commercially sold overseas, but they weren't sold in reality. 

451
00:33:49,073 --> 00:33:52,803
 The buyer withdrew their offer after seeing the finished product. 

452
00:33:52,803 --> 00:33:56,723
 Are there no buyers at all, even though they spent a fortune on it? 

453
00:33:56,723 --> 00:33:59,333
 Even if they said they spent ₩30 billion to produce the movie 

454
00:33:59,333 --> 00:34:01,983
 doesn't mean that movie is worth ₩30 billion. 

455
00:34:01,983 --> 00:34:05,143
 It appears there was a problem during the planning stage. 

456
00:34:05,143 --> 00:34:08,783
 Well, what do you have to say about the goods? 

457
00:34:08,783 --> 00:34:12,753
 Many of the goods they have are of inactive artists. 

458
00:34:12,753 --> 00:34:15,583
 Since these artists' contract period with People's Ent. hasn't expired, 

459
00:34:15,583 --> 00:34:18,483
 it isn't illegal for them to count as inventory of assets, 

460
00:34:18,483 --> 00:34:20,823
 but it means they likely won't sell them. 

461
00:34:20,823 --> 00:34:21,793
 What's the evidence? 

462
00:34:21,793 --> 00:34:24,933
 It'd be easy to prove by checking the artists' income tax return details. 

463
00:34:24,933 --> 00:34:28,263
 We can't do that. It would breach the Personal Information Act. 

464
00:34:28,263 --> 00:34:33,103
 Yes, so I viewed the company's withholding tax 

465
00:34:33,103 --> 00:34:35,943
 since that information was already made available. 

466
00:34:36,543 --> 00:34:38,823
 You're quite good. 

467
00:34:38,823 --> 00:34:40,753
 So? 

468
00:34:41,573 --> 00:34:44,003
 They don't have any up-to-date information. 

469
00:34:44,003 --> 00:34:47,053
 Since they have no profits from any artist, 

470
00:34:47,053 --> 00:34:49,923
 the company has also paid no money to their artists? 

471
00:34:49,923 --> 00:34:52,113
 Same goes for their tax payments 

472
00:34:52,113 --> 00:34:56,543
 since the taxes paid by a celebrity are directly correlated to their popularity. 

473
00:34:57,923 --> 00:35:01,213
 In other words, they are worthless products 

474
00:35:01,213 --> 00:35:04,203
 with nobody to buy them. 

475
00:35:04,203 --> 00:35:08,443
 Currently, People's Entertainment is about to go out of business. 

476
00:35:12,023 --> 00:35:13,853
I was going to tell you.

477
00:35:13,853 --> 00:35:18,093
When? After the auditing reports were finished?

478
00:35:18,093 --> 00:35:22,983
No way. You're not going to write this in the auditing report...

479
00:35:22,983 --> 00:35:25,453
You're not, right... right, Mr. Kang?

480
00:35:25,453 --> 00:35:27,993
If necessary, I should

481
00:35:27,993 --> 00:35:30,283
since that is my job.

482
00:35:31,343 --> 00:35:33,253
Mr. Kang.

483
00:35:35,043 --> 00:35:36,843
 What are you doing? 

484
00:35:36,843 --> 00:35:41,943
 If you help us out just this once, People's Entertainment can get back on its feet quickly! 

485
00:35:41,943 --> 00:35:45,273
I, Goo Joon Tak, was able to survive in this field because of my credibility.

486
00:35:45,273 --> 00:35:47,493
Really! If I can get just one big hit,

487
00:35:47,493 --> 00:35:50,943
I won't take any of that money for myself and take care of

488
00:35:50,943 --> 00:35:53,113
the company's financial issues once and for all.

489
00:35:53,113 --> 00:35:56,763
 We even found a way for us to survive. 

490
00:35:57,933 --> 00:36:00,743
- A way for you to survive? 
 - Yes!

491
00:36:02,573 --> 00:36:08,173
Sangah Group says they will pursue an M and A with my company.

492
00:36:08,173 --> 00:36:10,563
If that happens, 40 billion won't be a problem.

493
00:36:10,563 --> 00:36:12,853
The shares will skyrocket!

494
00:36:13,523 --> 00:36:16,583
Are you saying an M and A with Sangah Group?

495
00:36:16,583 --> 00:36:18,103
Yes!

496
00:36:19,353 --> 00:36:22,773
 The Deals Department Director seems to take a lot of interest in the Auditing Department. 

497
00:36:22,773 --> 00:36:24,723
 What do you mean "interest"? 

498
00:36:24,723 --> 00:36:29,113
 I just heard that one of my clients bought some of People's Entertainment's stocks. 

499
00:36:32,083 --> 00:36:36,913
 Why my company ended up like this is due to Sangah Group's third-generation son! 

500
00:36:36,913 --> 00:36:39,823
He doesn't have many stocks,

